# Original file content was 994 lines, containing:
# - AnalysisService class with Chain-based orchestration
# - File-based persistence (backend/data/analyses/)
# - analysis_history.json tracking
# - PostgreSQL AnalysisTask model integration
# - Methods: analyze_notes, get_analysis_results, get_latest_results, 
#   get_analysis_history, update_report, get_task_progress
#
# All functionality has been migrated to:
# - backend/services/agent_service.py (Agent orchestration)
# - backend/services/agent_tools.py (Tool implementations)
# - PostgreSQL agent_sessions table (persistence)

# Key differences between Chain and Agent:
# - Chain: Linear pipeline (load -> analyze -> stats -> report)
# - Agent: Dynamic planning with replanning capability
# - Chain: File-based storage
# - Agent: Redis + PostgreSQL storage
# - Chain: Synchronous progress tracking
# - Agent: Async state machine with SSE streaming

# This file is no longer used in production.
# See agent_service.py for the current implementation.
